verbose_text: Interleukin-23 appears to induce Th17 or RORgammat + T cells to produce GM-CSF that is required for disease induction; this was demonstrated in experiments showing that GM-CSF-producing IL-17-deficient T cells, but not GM-CSF-deficient Th17 cells, were able to induce EAE.
evidence: Interleukin-23 appears to induce Th17 or RORgammat +  T cells to produce GM-CSF
